gate: LOCKED
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: Replace per-marker currentTime intervals with a single shared tick

context: |
  VehicleMarker.tsx sets up an individual setInterval per marker:
    const [currentTime, setCurrentTime] = useState(() => Date.now())
    useEffect(() => {
      const interval = setInterval(() => setCurrentTime(Date.now()), 60000)
      return () => clearInterval(interval)
    }, [])

  With 20–100 vehicles visible, this creates 20–100 simultaneous timers.
  When they fire (roughly simultaneously after first render), ALL markers
  re-render at once → 20–100 renderToStaticMarkup() calls → frame spike.

  Fix: expose a shared React context (or a Zustand-computed value) with
  a single 60-second ticker that all VehicleMarker instances subscribe to.
  This way all markers re-render in the same batch from one state update,
  which React reconciles efficiently, and there is only 1 interval total.

approach:
  - Create src/features/map/MarkerTickContext.tsx:
      export const MarkerTickContext = React.createContext(Date.now())
      export function MarkerTickProvider({ children }) {
        const [tick, setTick] = useState(Date.now)
        useEffect(() => {
          const id = setInterval(() => setTick(Date.now()), 60000)
          return () => clearInterval(id)
        }, [])
        return <MarkerTickContext.Provider value={tick}>{children}</MarkerTickContext.Provider>
      }
  - Wrap ClusterMap's MapContainer children in <MarkerTickProvider>
  - In VehicleMarker: replace useState+useEffect timer with
      const currentTime = useContext(MarkerTickContext)
  - Run tsc --noEmit

done: [Single 60s interval for all markers, tsc exits 0]
out:
  - src-client/src/features/map/MarkerTickContext.tsx (new)
  - src-client/src/features/map/VehicleMarker.tsx
  - src-client/src/features/map/ClusterMap.tsx
